  <front>
    <title>RADIUS Identifier Attribute</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-chen-radext-extended-header-02"/>
    <author initials="E." surname="Chen" fullname="Enke Chen">
      <organization>Cisco Systems</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="N." surname="Shen" fullname="Naiming Shen">
      <organization>Cisco Systems</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="26" month="March" year="2017"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>The limitation with the one-octet "Identifier" field in the RADIUS
   packet is well known. In this document we propose extensions to the
   RADIUS protocol to address this fundamental limitation, and thus
   allowing for more efficient and more scalable implementations.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
